# Walkthrough - Prompt Caching Implementation

I have successfully implemented **Prompt Caching** in the `new_llm_v2` project. This optimization "harnesses" the same boundary pattern used in the Claude Code codebase to reduce API costs and latency.

## Changes Made

### 1. Configuration Constants
In [config.py](file:///c:/Users/CHip/OneDrive%20-%20Chipspirit%20Technologies%20Private%20Limited/Desktop/AM/24/SPI/anti_gravity/anthropic-leaked-source-code-main/new_llm_v3/new_llm_v2/config.py), I added the necessary constants to enable the feature:
- `ANTHROPIC_CACHE_BETA_HEADER`: The beta header required by Anthropic's API (`prompt-caching-2024-07-31`).
- `ENABLE_PROMPT_CACHING`: A toggle to turn the feature on or off.

### 2. Header Injection
In [rag_chain.py](file:///c:/Users/CHip/OneDrive%20-%20Chipspirit%20Technologies%20Private%20Limited/Desktop/AM/24/SPI%20/anti_gravity/anthropic-leaked-source-code-main/new_llm_v3/new_llm_v2/rag_chain.py), the `get_llm` function now includes the `anthropic-beta` header in every call to OpenRouter.

### 3. Partitioned System Prompt
The core of the optimization is in how the prompt is structured. I refactored the single `SYSTEM_PROMPT` into a multi-block structure:

| Block Type | Content | Caching Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Static (CORE)** | AI instructions, persona, and rules. | **Cached** (`ephemeral`) |
| **Dynamic (CONTEXT)** | The retrieved code/PDF chunks (`{context}`). | **Uncached** |

This ensures that the "Rules" are only processed once per session, while the "Data" is processed fresh as needed.

## Technical Details

The new `build_rag_chain` logic uses a structured `SystemMessage` compatible with LangChain and OpenRouter:

```python
system_message = {
    "role": "system",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": CORE_INSTRUCTIONS,
            "cache_control": {"type": "ephemeral"} # The "Locker" marker
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": CONTEXT_PROMPT # The dynamic context {context}
        }
    ]
}
```

## Expected Results
- **Cost Reduction:** Up to **90% savings** on the instruction tokens after the first turn.
- **Improved Latency:** Faster "First Token" response time in long-running chats.
- **Graceful Failure:** If a model doesn't support caching, these tags are safely ignored.

